dfischer.utils

Class LoadtestExternalRemoteResourcesDataRecord

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.utils.LoadtestExternalRemoteResourcesDataRecord

  • public class LoadtestExternalRemoteResourcesDataRecord
extends java.lang.Object
    Definition of an additional, external resource which is already located on a (remote) load generator (Exec Agent) and is needed when executing a load test job. Typically such an external resource is a Java library file (*.jar file) which is used by a plug-in. However, also any other file type can be specified. A copy of the file will be created in the job directory of the corresponding load test job.
    See Also:
    LoadtestExternalResources

      • LoadtestExternalRemoteResourcesDataRecord

        public LoadtestExternalRemoteResourcesDataRecord(long remoteResourceId,
                                         java.lang.String remoteFilePath,
                                         boolean addToClassPath,
                                         boolean addToXbootclasspath)
        Create a new instance an initialize the instance with the data of the remote file that will be copied to the job directory of the corresponding load test job. Note: the resource type is implicitely configured to the value REMOTE_RESOURCE_TYPE_FILE.
        Parameters:
        remoteResourceId - unique ID that is assigned to the instance
        remoteFilePath - absolute path of the remote file on the load generator (Exec Agent)
        addToClassPath - if set to true: add the file to the Java CLASSPATH on the load generator when executing a load test job
        addToXbootclasspath - if set to true: add the file to the Java -Xbootclasspath/p: on the load generator when executing a load test job
        See Also:
        REMOTE_RESOURCE_TYPE_FILE
